title: Nirbhay
subTitle: An innocent man faces wrongful imprisonment for murder, but years later uncovers a shocking conspiracy. Subsequently, determined to avenge his past, he embarks on a relentless quest for vengeance.

title: Vardaan Devi Maa Ka
subTitle: Tarigonda Vengamamba, an 18th-century poetess, devotes her life serving Lord Venkateshwara. She starts writing numerous songs for him and also considers him as her husband.

title: Maa Ki Mamta
subTitle: Thakur Dharam seeks a nurse for his son after his wife passes away; the wife of one of his farm laborers agrees to help him.

title: Mahabharat
subTitle: A dynastic struggle between the collateral branches of the Kuru clan, the Kauravas and Pandavas, for the throne of Hastinapur leads to the Kurukshetra War.

title: Bhoot Returns
subTitle: Tarun and Namrata move into a luxurious bungalow with Taman and Nimmi, their son and daughter respectively. However, strange occurrences start taking place and they must escape in order to survive.

title: Naseeb
subTitle: The lives of friends Namdev, Raghu, Damu and Jaggi take a turn for the worse when they win a lottery. Raghu and Damu murder Jaggi and frame Namdev who later returns to seek revenge.

title: Shoorveer
subTitle: Siddharth, a fashion editor who hates horses, decides to venture into the world of horse racing to impress the girl of his dreams.

title: Doodh Ka Karz
subTitle: When her snake charmer husband is falsely accused of theft and beaten to death, a widow raises her son to seek revenge, with the help of a loyal snake.

title: Kasam Hindustan Ki
subTitle: Dhuruvan is a forest ranger who trains NCC cadets. On a trek with five college girls, he stumbles upon a gang of terrorists who plan to foil a rocket launch by ISRO.

title: Mard
subTitle: Azad, a wealthy prosperous king, is locked in a dungeon by General Dyer who wants to take over his kingdom. Years later, Azad's son comes to his father's rescue and puts an end to Dyer's tyranny.

title: Mahaabali
subTitle: Seenu's debt-driven escape to Dubai accidentally reroutes him to Hyderabad. Upon arrival, a shocking discovery leads him to orchestrate a cunning plan.

title: Mahaabali

title: Tathagat Buddha
subTitle: Lord Buddha was born as Prince Siddhartha Gautama in Kapilavastu, Nepal, in the 6th century B.C. Renouncing worldly pleasures, he left his wife and son to seek salvation.

title: Adharm
subTitle: Mr Verma's decision to disown his son Jaggan sparks a vow of retribution. Years later, Jaggan devises a plan to destroy his family and retaliate against his father.

title: Daraar
subTitle: Raj Malhotra, a wealthy man, falls for Priya. However, things get complicated when Vikram, Priya's abusive husband, enters the frame.

title: Chaalbaaz
subTitle: Anju endures mistreatment at home, whereas her long-separated twin Manju boldly navigates life's challenges. By some quirk of fate, they end up trading places, and their worlds erupt in chaos.

title: Koyla
subTitle: Silenced by a piece of smouldering coal in childhood, Shankar endures a life of slavery until love compels him to seek his voice, freedom, and long-overdue revenge.

title: Bade Miyan Chote Miyan
subTitle: In a strange faraway town, small-time crooks Bade and Chote stir up double trouble and leave their policemen look-alikes flapping around like headless chickens.

title: Krack
subTitle: Three delinquents attempt to outwit a resolute police officer, underestimating his clever methods and unwavering dedication to law enforcement.

title: Karan Arjun
subTitle: Karan and Arjun, two brothers driven by revenge, are murdered by their uncle while seeking justice for their father's death. However, they resurrect years later to settle their unfinished score.

title: Encounter Shankar
subTitle: Post his transfer to a village, an encounter specialist sets out to stop a crime boss who wants to build a power plant in the region despite strong public opposition.

title: Encounter Shankar

title: Swarnakamalam
subTitle: Meenakshi, a young classical dancer who was born in a family of artists, is bitter about the lack of opportunity in India. However, Chandrashekhar changes her outlook and helps her grow.

title: Akbar Birbal
subTitle: Clever Birbal aids Emperor Akbar in witty adventures, solving puzzles and delivering justice across Mughal India, unfolding tales of wisdom and humor.

title: Insaniyat Ke Devta
subTitle: Two friends, Balbir and Anwar, join forces to defeat an influential tycoon who wishes to destroy an ashram and use the property to further his own selfish purposes.

title: Fillers
subTitle: A comprehensive compilation of promotional videos and trailers of Bollywood movies featuring popular actors and actresses.

title: I Killed Bapu
subTitle: Nathuram Godse becomes one of the most hated men in the country after he assassinates Mahatma Gandhi. When he has his day in court, he explains his thoughts and motivations behind the crime.

title: Sandwich
subTitle: Sher Singh has two wives, Nisha and Sweety, and juggles his time between them. However, when his two wives cross paths, his troubles increase manifold leading to hilarious situations.

title: Kishen Kanhaiya
subTitle: Separated at birth, Kishen and Kanhaiya grow up in different worlds, one in opulent luxury, the other in poverty. Fate reunites them as they fight together to end injustice.

title: Jaan
subTitle: Karan is hired to kill Kajal, the granddaughter of a police commissioner, but they end up falling in love. However, fate tests their bond when Karan's true intentions are revealed.

title: Dacait
subTitle: After being mercilessly beaten and abandoned to die, a young man is rescued by a band of dacoits, who nurse him back to health in their hidden lair.

title: Baaghi
subTitle: Determined to rescue his former love, the ruggedly handsome Ronny confronts his enemies with a flurry of powerful roundhouse kicks and bone-crushing punches.

title: Lal Baadshah
subTitle: Lal Singh, a righteous and helpful man, clashes against Dayal Singh, a powerful personality. However, things get complicated when a hidden treasure is involved and Lal's tragic past is disclosed.
